flowRoot.flowPara: Selecting one of too many options is a usual interaction. The selectRoller should only be used when there are more than 3 options or when those options cannot fit in a buttonRow or buttonColumn. If the number of items increases more than those that can fit in one screen a drill-down structure is recommended,
The current item become semi-bold and animates (relatively to the list) to it's position in the list.
If possible, the whole list animates to a position higher up so that our current item still stays at the same place.
The list can wrap around like the contextRoller
